  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where can I get scholarship for data science in Asia?",
  "response": "Securing scholarships for data science in Asia can significantly reduce the financial burden of pursuing your studies. Various institutions, governments, and organizations offer scholarships for students interested in data science. Here are some potential sources:\n\n1. **Universities and Colleges**:\n    - **National University of Singapore (NUS)**: NUS offers a range of scholarships for both undergraduate and postgraduate programs, including those in data science.\n    - **University of Tokyo**: Scholarships for international students, including those studying data science, are available at the University of Tokyo.\n    - **KAIST (Korea Advanced Institute of Science and Technology)**: Offers scholarships for international students, including those pursuing data science-related programs.\n    - **Hong Kong University of Science and Technology (HKUST)**: Provides various scholarships for international students and graduate programs.\n    - **Indian Institute of Technology (IIT)**: Different IITs offer scholarships for students enrolling in data science programs, including IIT Bombay and IIT Delhi.\n\n2. **Government Scholarships**:\n    - **Singapore Government Scholarships**: The Ministry of Education (MOE) offers various scholarships for international students.\n    - **Japanese Government (MEXT) Scholarships**: The Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology offers scholarships for international students in various fields including data science.\n    - **Chinese Government Scholarships**: Offered by the China Scholarship Council for international students, covering data science and related fields.\n    - **Korean Government Scholarship Program (KGSP)**: Offered by NIIED for international students including graduate studies in data science.\n\n3. **Private Organizations and Foundations**:\n    - **Aga Khan Foundation Scholarships**: For postgraduate students from selected developing countries, it may include data science programs.\n    - **Japan-IMF Scholarship Program for Asia**: For students in various fields including data science by the IMF and Japanese government.\n    - **Google Scholarships**: Google often offers scholarships for students in computer science and related fields, including data science, through various programs in Asia.\n\n4. **Online and Global Platforms**:\n    - **Coursera, edX Scholarships**: Sometimes offer financial aid and scholarships for their data science programs in collaboration with universities.\n    - **Fulbright Program**: Offers scholarships for students from various countries to study in the US, including data science-related programs, which can include exchange programs or study abroad options in Asia.\n\nWhen applying for these scholarships, make sure to check the specific eligibility criteria, application deadlines, and required documentation. It is advisable to frequently visit the respective websites or contact the administrative offices for the most up-to-date information.",
